The touch of genius is over them all, everywhere, from the rich eye of the retriever to the wasted turnip leaves, Yet there is no mere cleverness, no traces of handi- work 3 you are not made to think of work at all, till you have got your fill of pleasure and surprise, and then you wonder what cunning hrain, and eye, and finger could have got so much out of so little, and so common. ”
